</p>
<p>The delivery method itself is crucial. A handwritten note conveys a deeper sense of personal investment, while a phone call allows for immediate emotional connection.  Regardless of the method chosen, ensure your tone is gentle, respectful, and avoids judgment or unsolicited advice.  Remember, your role is to offer comfort and support, not to solve the problem of grief.  Focus on acknowledging their pain and letting them know you're there for them, however they need you.</p>
    

